TY  - JOUR
AU  - Schmitt-Grohé, Stephanie
AU  - Uribe, Martín
T1  - Multiple Equilibria in Open Economies with Collateral Constraints
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdaa023
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 88
IS  - 2
SP  - 969
EP  - 1001
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - This article establishes the existence of multiple equilibria in infinite-horizon open economy models in which the value of tradable and non-tradable endowments serves as collateral. In this environment, the economy displays self-fulfilling financial crises in which pessimistic views about the value of collateral induce agents to deleverage. Under plausible calibrations, there exist equilibria with underborrowing. This result stands in contrast to the overborrowing result stressed in the related literature. Underborrowing emerges in the present context because in economies that are prone to self-fulfilling financial crises, individual agents engage in excessive precautionary savings as a way to self-insure.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdaa023
ER  - 



